## Description {#details}

This file defines late ObjC ARC optimizations.

ARC stands for Automatic Reference Counting and is a system for managing reference counts for objects in Objective C.

This specific file mainly deals with &#96;â€˜contracting`&#39; multiple lower level operations into singular higher level operations through pattern matching.

WARNING: This file knows about certain library functions. It recognizes them by name, and hardwires knowledge of their semantics.

WARNING: This file knows about how certain Objective-C library functions are used. Naive LLVM IR transformations which would otherwise be behavior-preserving may break these assumptions.

<Link id="l00310" /><CodeLine lineNumber="310"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00311" /><CodeLine lineNumber="311"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Attempt to merge an objc&#95;release with a store, load, and objc&#95;retain to form</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// an objc&#95;storeStrong. An objc&#95;storeStrong:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00313" /><CodeLine lineNumber="313"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   objc&#95;storeStrong(i8&#42;&#42; %old&#95;ptr, i8&#42; new&#95;value)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// is equivalent to the following IR sequence:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   ; Load old value.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   %old&#95;value = load i8&#42;&#42; %old&#95;ptr               (1)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   ; Increment the new value and then release the old value. This must occur</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   ; in order in case old&#95;value releases new&#95;value in its destructor causing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00323" /><CodeLine lineNumber="323"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   ; us to potentially have a dangling ptr.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00324" /><CodeLine lineNumber="324"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   tail call i8&#42; @objc&#95;retain(i8&#42; %new&#95;value)    (2)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   tail call void @objc&#95;release(i8&#42; %old&#95;value)  (3)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00326" /><CodeLine lineNumber="326"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00327" /><CodeLine lineNumber="327"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   ; Store the new&#95;value into old&#95;ptr</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00328" /><CodeLine lineNumber="328"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   store i8&#42; %new&#95;value, i8&#42;&#42; %old&#95;ptr           (4)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00329" /><CodeLine lineNumber="329"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00330" /><CodeLine lineNumber="330"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The safety of this optimization is based around the following</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00331" /><CodeLine lineNumber="331"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// considerations:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00332" /><CodeLine lineNumber="332"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00333" /><CodeLine lineNumber="333"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  1 We are forming the store strong at the store. Thus to perform this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     optimization it must be safe to move the retain, load, and release to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00335" /><CodeLine lineNumber="335"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     (4).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00336" /><CodeLine lineNumber="336"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  2 We need to make sure that any re-orderings of (1), (2), (3), (4) are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00337" /><CodeLine lineNumber="337"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     safe.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00338" /><CodeLine lineNumber="338"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ObjCARCContract::tryToContractReleaseIntoStoreStrong(</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instruction">Instruction</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a239c4ac35d6028bfacaed4018d0488faab8e7b465df7c5979dc731d06e84ce2cf">Release</a>, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a0c27cc387928f22d241825cf0fb67ade">inst&#95;iterator</a> &amp;Iter,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/densemap">DenseMap&lt;BasicBlock &#42;, ColorVector&gt;</a> &amp;BlockColors) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// See if we are releasing something that we just loaded.</span></CodeLine>
